codex
The patch lands the schema and node-importance path, but edge confidence is not actually applied to graph-arm retrieval and the new explain fields are not surfaced through existing SDK bindings. These are functional gaps in the advertised F9 mechanism.

Full review comments:

- [P2] Apply edge confidence to graph-arm hits — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/0.8.16-slice-5-20260708T114929Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:6179-6181
  When the weighted search uses `use_graph_arm=true`, graph-arm `SearchHit.id` is the reached node's `canonical_nodes.write_cursor`, while the confidence value lives on the traversed `canonical_edges.write_cursor`. Looking up `canonical_edges` by `h.id` therefore never finds the edge confidence for normal graph-arm node hits, so confidence-bearing edges do not affect ranking or explain output in the scenario this feature is meant to cover.

- [P2] Propagate F9 explain fields to bindings — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/0.8.16-slice-5-20260708T114929Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:1299-1308
  Adding `importance` and `confidence` here only exposes the new score components through the Rust engine type; the existing Python and N-API `PerHitExplain::from_rust` mirrors still copy only the old fields, so `search_explained` callers in those bindings cannot observe the F9 contribution even when it is present. Since the existing explain surface is already exported through those SDKs, these new fields need to be added to the binding structs/converters as part of the same change.
The patch lands the schema and node-importance path, but edge confidence is not actually applied to graph-arm retrieval and the new explain fields are not surfaced through existing SDK bindings. These are functional gaps in the advertised F9 mechanism.

